# The Second Law

A book by GMR

"Fathers shall not be put to death because of their children, nor shall children be put to death because of their fathers. Each one shall be put to death for his own sin." - Deuteronomy 24:16

# Prologue

It was a nice morning in August, nice enough that only two people in Brazil dared to think about nuclear bombs: the president, who thought the country didn't had enough, and the president's son, who sometimes wished his father died by one. For the other 245.3 million brazilians, the thought of a nuclear bomb didn't even crossed their heads that day. Not once, not even when the gamma rays of said bombs did. And this is the story surrounding that fateful day.
